CatDescriptText: Mrs. Mable Jackson, house keeper, 838 Frances Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the visit of the Russian ruler, Khrushchev, will promote world peace?" answer reads: "I don't see where it will help. IN fact, because the Russians are trying to get here, I think that we should try to keep them away.  I feel that we will be hurt."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mable Jackson wearing eyeglasses and medallion patterned blouse, standing outside of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
